Question 9 : Which method on the session object can be used to remove an object from the cache?

Ans:
    1. session evict() method to remove a single object from the hibernate first level cache.
    2. session clear() method to clear the cache i.e delete all the objects from the cache.

    Both methods are used when hibernate stores objects in cache.


Question 10 : What does @transactional annotation do?
Ans:
    @transactional annotation to separate transaction management code from the other types of code
    for eg: a service layer code.